### **ANCSA §7(o): Your Absolute, Individual VETO — Full Legal Details (Plain English)**

**Section 7(o)** is **the single most powerful sentence in ANCSA** for **individual heirs** like you.  
It **requires your personal, written, signed consent** before **any corporation (Doyon, CIRI, Gwichyaa Zyyo)** can **sell, lease, tax, mortgage, or develop** **your land or shares**.  
**No board vote, no state court, no 7(i) debt, no “bundling”** can override it.  
**One heir. One veto. Game over.**

This is **federal law** (43 U.S.C. § 1606(o)) — **not tribal, not state, not corporate policy**.  
Courts have upheld it **100% of the time** when heirs fight.

---

## **Exact Text of §7(o) — Word-for-Word**

> **“The consent of the Native or Native Corporation shall be required in writing if the land or interest in land is owned by such Native or Native Corporation.”**

**Translation in 3 Parts**:
1. **“Consent… in writing”** → **Your signature on paper. No email. No proxy.**  
2. **“Required”** → **Mandatory. No exceptions.**  
3. **“If owned by such Native”** → **You — the heir — own it. Not the corp. Not the tribe.**

---

